intro: Freycinetia milnei, commonly known as the New Zealand freycinetia, is a species of flowering plant in the family Cyclanthaceae. It is native to New Zealand and is characterized by its distinctive, narrow, strap-like leaves. The plant produces small, clustered flowers that are typically greenish-white in color. Freycinetia milnei is often found growing in coastal and lowland areas, preferring well-drained soils. It is a relatively rare species, with limited distribution and is of interest to botanists due to its unique morphology and ecological significance.
